
[1]soreness

   SO'RENESS, n. [from sore.]

   1. The tenderness of any part of an animal body, which renders it
   extremely susceptible of pain from pressure; as the soreness of a boil,
   an abscess or wound.

   2. Figuratively, tenderness of mind, or susceptibility of mental pain.
